Index Fit Report

North Atlantic Swordfish MSE

Adrian Hordyk adrian@bluematterscience.com

April 23, 2020

1 Introduction

This report summarizes the fits across the 288 OMs from the uncertainty grid to the 14 indices from the North Atlantic swordfish.

2 Indices and Fits

The following plots show the observed index (black solid dots - left panel) and the observed index adjusted for an assumed 1% annual increase in catchability (black solid dots - right panel) for the 14 indices, with the model fits from each OM shown as colored lines (red = no environmental covariate, blue = an environmental covariate).

3 Summary of Statistical Properties

3.1 No Increase in Catchability

Histograms of the statistical properties of the log-deviations from the fits to the 14 indices, including auto-correlation (ac), correlation (cor), root-mean-square-error (rmse), and standard deviation (sd), for the 144 OMs using the observed indices.

3.2 1% Annual Increase in Catchability

Histograms of the statistical properties of the log-deviations from the fits to the 14 indices, including auto-correlation (ac), correlation (cor), root-mean-square-error (rmse), and standard deviation (sd), for the 144 OMs using the observed indices adjusted for an assumed 1% annual increase in catchability.
